task.summary: Default task
Refactor to Gradle Multi-Module project: - Move src to app/src - Introduce Kotlin JS project as frontend for our AI Chat server

Refactor WebSocket handling and improve ChatRoutes interface
Refactored WebSocket client to enhance connection management and error handling by using flows. Updated ChatRoutes to support asynchronous AI repository initialization. These changes improve code clarity, maintainability, and resilience.

Refactor password handling to use Password value class
Replaced plain String representation of passwords with the Password value class for better type safety and encapsulation. This change affects login, user creation, password updates, and verification processes across tests and the main application. Ensured to update all relevant logic and tests accordingly.

Add initial Kotlin Multiplatform project for Compose-based app
This commit adds a Compose Multiplatform project targeting iOS, Web (WASM), and common platforms. It includes base UI components, a platform-specific implementation for greeting functionality, and the necessary Gradle and Xcode configurations. The setup enables shared code across platforms while incorporating platform-specific UI and resources.

Replace Greeting system with Chat feature in Compose app
Removed the Greeting and platform-specific implementations and introduced a chat interface with message bubbles, input handling, and a demo repository for simulated AI responses. Integrated Compose UI components for messaging and added the necessary model, ViewModel, and repository classes to support the chat system.

Remove unused iOS, and frontend modules.
This commit deletes the obsolete assets and code, `iosApp` module, and frontend-related resources. It also simplifies the project configuration, refactors chat state management, and updates the build scripts accordingly for a cleaner and more focused codebase.

Refactor AI module and integrate LangChain4j with Kotlin Coroutines.
The AI module has been restructured for a clearer separation of concerns. LangChain4j integration with Kotlin Coroutines enables seamless streaming using Flow APIs. This also adds metric tracking and changes to routes and services for improved scalability and maintainability.

Refactor AI module and integrate LangChain4j with Kotlin Coroutines.
The AI module has been restructured for a clearer separation of concerns. LangChain4j integration with Kotlin Coroutines enables seamless streaming using Flow APIs. This also adds metric tracking and changes to routes and services for improved scalability and maintainability.

Refactor AI module and integrate LangChain4j with Kotlin Coroutines.
The AI module has been restructured for a clearer separation of concerns. LangChain4j integration with Kotlin Coroutines enables seamless streaming using Flow APIs. This also adds metric tracking and changes to routes and services for improved scalability and maintainability.

Refactor AI services into modular components
Reorganized the AI system into separate, modular services to enhance maintainability and flexibility. Introduced `AiService` and `DocumentService` to handle AI responses and document ingestion respectively, replacing the monolithic `AiRepo`. Added coroutine-based streaming support with `langchain4j-kotlinx-coroutines`.

Remove legacy chat components and integrate WebSocket-based architecture
This commit transitions from the old chat implementation to a WebSocket-based approach, removing all previous UI components, repositories, and models. It introduces a WebSocketChatRepository, updated `ChatScreen` UI, and a revamped `ChatViewModel` for real-time communication. Additionally, server routes and configurations have been adjusted for WebSocket support and session handling.

Refactor document ingestion and extend PDF handling support
Moved `track` Flow extension to a dedicated file for reuse and refactored document ingestion logic in `DocumentService` to add support for streaming PDF uploads. Added SSE support for chat routes and introduced the Apache PDFBox library for processing PDFs.

Refactor document ingestion and extend PDF handling support
Moved `track` Flow extension to a dedicated file for reuse and refactored document ingestion logic in `DocumentService` to add support for streaming PDF uploads. Added SSE support for chat routes and introduced the Apache PDFBox library for processing PDFs.

Add OAuth2 support with Keycloak and replace JWT-based auth
Replaced JWT authentication with OAuth2 using Keycloak for better security and session management. Added configuration for OAuth2 in both the application and Docker setup. Removed unused JWT-related code and updated routes, sessions, and dependencies accordingly.

Add OAuth2 support with Keycloak and replace JWT-based auth
Replaced JWT authentication with OAuth2 using Keycloak for better security and session management. Added configuration for OAuth2 in both the application and Docker setup. Removed unused JWT-related code and updated routes, sessions, and dependencies accordingly.

Add OAuth2 support with Keycloak and replace JWT-based auth
Replaced JWT authentication with OAuth2 using Keycloak for better security and session management. Added configuration for OAuth2 in both the application and Docker setup. Removed unused JWT-related code and updated routes, sessions, and dependencies accordingly.

Refactor authentication system and improve session handling
Replaced "oauth" with "auth" in configuration and added encryption/signing keys for session security. Changed `userId` type to String and updated `UserSession` structure for JWT decoding. Introduced support for server-sent events and cleaned up ChatScreen formatting.

Update Keycloak user and integrate session-based userId
Added detailed attributes (name, email) for the Keycloak user configuration to improve user representation in the system. Replaced hardcoded `1L` with `session.userId` in `ChatRoutes` to correctly handle interactions based on the authenticated user's session.

Remove unused features and improve OAuth integration.
Deleted unreferenced authorization code, tests, and helpers. Enabled Prometheus and Grafana services in Docker Compose. Refactored application module configuration and improved dependency handling. Updated OAuth configuration and streamlined AI service initialization for better modularity.

Refactor Spotless with KtFmt for improved consistency and readability
This commit applies formatting adjustments for cleaner code, ensures consistent indentation, and improves alignment across files. Unnecessary imports are removed.

Refactor project structure and consolidate modules
Moved `composeApp` functionality into `app` and introduced `backend` module. Updated build configurations, dependencies, and file paths to align with this restructured project layout for better modularity and maintainability.

Refactor PDF processing to use `ApachePdfBoxDocumentParser`.
Replaced the `pdfbox` library with `langchain4j-pdf` for PDF processing. Updated the `DocumentService` to use `ApachePdfBoxDocumentParser` for improved handling and streamlined ingestion of PDF files. Removed unused dependencies and adjusted related build configurations.

Remove unused dependencies and improve code formatting.
Cleaned up unused imports and dependencies, including `kotlin-test` and PDFBox. Made minor formatting adjustments for better readability and consistency. These changes simplify the codebase and improve maintainability.
